Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough
@water{} to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{10-15%minutes}. Reserve 1/2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and keep covered off heat until ready to mash in Step 6.

While potatoes cook, heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning
too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert),
> you can get started on them now!

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Drain @corn{1%unit};
pat dry with @paper towels{}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit},
separating whites from greens.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil{}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in pan used for bacon over high heat. Add corn and
cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and lightly charred in spots,
~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Heat pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Once hot, add a
drizzle of @oil{}. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per
side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wash out pan.

Melt 2 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in pan used for corn over medium heat. Add
scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Sprinkle with
@flour{2%tablespoon} and stir vigorously to combine.

Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit} and @water{1%cup}; bring to a
simmer and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> If the gravy is too thick, add more water a splash at a time.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use pan used for steak here.

To pot with potatoes, add @sour cream{1%packet} and @plain butter{2%tablespoon}.

> If you like truffle, feel free to swap in the truffle butter for the
> plain butter and skip serving it on the side!

Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of
reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve mashed potatoes, bacon, green beans, corn, scallion greens, gravy,
@crispy fried onions{1%unit}, @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded),
@truffle butter{2%tablespoon}, and remaining @sour cream{1%packet} family style
for everyone to build their own mashed potato bowls.

> Serve broccoli alongside mashed potato bar.

> Thinly slice steak against the grain. Serve alongside mashed potato bar.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.